Introduction
All of us have been through a tough 2020. Thousands of small business in the cities shut down. However, for someone 2021 could be a good time to invest in small business accelerating the local economy regression. Our client is planning to open a restaurant in Vancouver, BC. But the location of restaurant and type of food served are unknown. Client hope that we are able to find out the popularity of food in each neighbourhood, and provide a relevant recommendation of address. Certain steps we are going to walk through to reach a final conclusion, such as retrieving data, analyzing, results, recommendations. Matrix would be helpful to compare types of restaurant and neighbourhood. Also, average rental fee will be considered, helps client to control the cost and maximize the return.

Vancouver is a major city in the western Canada with densest and most diverse population. The city Vancouver had 631,486 people, and there were 2,463,431 population in Greater Vancouver Area by 2016.  The Greater Vancouver Area consists of several small urban, like Richmond, Burnabay, Coquitlam, Langley city and so on. (Wikipedia, 2021)
 
Source of Data
Data frame will be used for model retrieved from website. Two sources of data are shown below:
    • Postal code for each city in Greater Vancouver Area source from geoname website. (Geonames, 2021) This data could help locating the geo-infomation such as latitude and longtitude.

    • Data frame shows the population of Greater Vancouver Area, data will be processed and refined  to merge into previous geonames data frame. (Statistics Canada, 2016)

